My wife and I got married here in November and everything was excellent. Sonia, Nikki, and the entire staff were extremely helpful and informative throughout the process. They are very easy to work with. The venue itself is beautiful, historic, and its location is convenient. All of the food was outstanding, from the cocktail hour through dinner and dessert. There was plenty of food and servers to pass it around, and the quality of the cuisine is phenomenal. You will have many choices for your menu and the tasting is a fun time, although it was hard to choose. Overall we would absolutely recommend India House/Masterpiece Caterers to anyone who is planning a wedding in Manhattan.

I’m being generous with the one star... As beautiful as the location is; if the food and service are not up to par, it is just a waste of money to go there.  The India House at 1 Hanover Square is by far one if the worst places I’ve ever eaten. A group of approximately 200 people were there for a company party and upon arriving to the cocktail hour there were two half bars with limited choices and no mixers others than seltzer water and ginger ale.  The turkey and corn beef were over cooked and extremely dry. All the rest seemed as if they were at one time frozen and reheated by microwave.  The dinner, which took place on a different floor was atrocious!  Once seated for dinner, that staff took everyone’s orders... it took a little over an hour to get our food... there was no wine or water at the table and we had to go back upstairs to get drinks... The wait staff got everyone’s order and temperature wrong. The Salmon was dry and the New York strip was like a tasteless hockey puck.  Dessert (cookies/brownies) was served back upstairs and no one offered coffee or tea... I would never recommend this place to anyone. Don’t be fooled by the building’s beauty and historical significance.  You’ll have a Better meal at the Halal truck parked three blocks away.

We simply cannot say enough wonderful things about Kevin, Nikki, and the team at India House/1 Hanover Square. They made our entire wedding planning process an absolute dream. Their commitment to hospitality is unmatched, especially in New York City. Our guests were completely blown away and are still raving about the attentiveness of the staff and the delicious food. Many said it was the best food they had ever had at a wedding, including our vegan and vegetarian friends! Plus, the venue itself is absolutely stunning! It is the perfect place for couples looking for something unique with a classic New York feel. Kevin also worked with us to give us what we wanted while helping us stay within our budget, and was very responsive. We truly feel like Kevin, Nikki, and the team became a part of our family throughout the process. We would highly recommend them a thousand times over!

I came here for a wedding and while the building and decor are both relatively nice (albeit pretty cold on all levels the entire night), it was the dinner that earned this one-star rating. As a non-meat-eater, I had to watch everyone around me receive plates with a large portion of beef and chicken with accompanying sides (all of which was so-so according to those at my table) and then be giving the vegan option. Apparently the chef thinks that vegan means rabbit food because I was served a single boiled carrot with undercooked and unseasoned rice covered in what tasted like canned spaghetti sauce. Needless to say I was quite hungry for the rest of the night and just can't get over how utterly disappointing that "dinner" was.

THIS PLACE IS THE BEST!!! You cannot go wrong. I couldn't have dreamt a better wedding.  The service, food, decor, ambiance, and the attention you get from India House (1 Hanover Sq) is unparalleled.  My friends and family were blown away.  Everyone was so impressed and said this was the best wedding they have attended.  And I really give India House the credit for this.  Their service is flawless.  And the venue captures the energy, elegance and class of a NYC wedding.  The venue includes the catering service of Masterpiece Caterers which includes the food, liquor, and cake. The cake is from the Financier and its beyond delicious. And I can't say enough good things about Adam Hartofilis (Director of Catering at India House).  He is a perfectionist.  Trust me when I say he cares more about your wedding than even you do.  Somehow he'd improve on ideas we had discussed and make things better.  On the wedding day, he made my family rehearse their parts and reminded them the order of things which made the wedding perfect. And Adam really does fulfill all your wishes.  Adam is AWESOME.  Trust your wedding plans to Adam and you will be amazed.  Thank you so much to everybody at India House, especially Adam.

My wedding on 3.12.16 at India House was everything I wanted. The venue (Blue Bar & Hanover Room) were intimate and perfect spaces for my guest (90 total). I held my ceremony, cocktail hour and reception there. I even used their bridal suite to get ready with my wedding party. The food was delicious and the service was exceptional. I was amazed when I found this gem in NYC which was perfect for my "Old New York" theme. I was nervous because another wedding was being held at India house on the same day.  The staff did an amazing job with making sure the two events would not impact each other, because they did not. They were great to work with and very accommodating. A special thank you to Jessica Oliva for making the planning process painless. She was professional, responsive and helpful in recommending vendors such as musicians for my ceremony. Booking India House and Master Caters to host my special day was the best decision I made and I highly recommend it.
